                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> FARNLAY and WOODHOUSE. <persName>
                           <forename>Roger</forename> de
                        <surname>Notton</surname>
                        </persName> grants to <persName>
                           <forename>Baldewin</forename> the <surname>Teuton</surname>
                        </persName> the whole
                  of his land of <placeName key="place_103162">Farnlay</placeName> and <placeName key="place_103406">Whudehuse</placeName> within and without the village, being 3 carucates, the fourth of the knight's fee, also the
                  homage and service of <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> de
                        <surname>Ruelay</surname>
                        </persName> and his heirs, paying yearly three shillings. For this gift the said
                  Baldwin and <persName>
                           <forename>Margery</forename> his wife</persName> quit-claim to the said Roger all right in land at
                  <placeName key="place_103341">Silkeston</placeName> which she had by the name of dowry of <persName>
                           <forename>Gilbert</forename> de <surname>Notton</surname>
                        </persName> Roger's father and formerly her husband. 
                  (<origDate notBefore="1233" notAfter="1240" precision="low">c. 1233-40</origDate>.) 
                  . </p>
